    <section id="projects" class="projects-section">
        <div class="container">
            <h2 class="section-title">Selected Projects – Driving Efficiency Through Data & Process Innovation</h2>

            <div class="project-card">
                <h3>Nationwide Legacy Data Digitization & Debit Card System Rollout</h3>
                <h4>State Bank of Hyderabad</h4>
                <p><strong>Role:</strong> Lead, Data Digitization & System Integration Team</p>
                <p class="context"><strong>Context:</strong> The introduction of a new debit card system in 1999 required the digitization of millions of customer accounts, including sensitive details, signatures (some 40-50 years old), and photographs, from 360 branches across India. The existing manual processes were highly error-prone, time-consuming, and lacked data integrity, hindering the successful implementation of core banking and ATM/debit card systems. Physical archives presented significant environmental challenges.</p>
                <div class="details-grid">
                    <div>
                        <h4>My Role & Responsibilities</h4>
                        <ul>
                            <li>Led a team of 40 data entry and verification specialists.</li>
                            <li>Directed the end-to-end data lifecycle: meticulous acquisition, structuring, editing, sorting, and integration of customer, account, signature, and photo data into new core banking and ATM/debit card systems.</li>
                            <li>Designed and implemented rigorous quality control protocols for high-volume data entry and scanning.</li>
